Comment: Dymadon, Panadol Drops, Paralgin Jnr Elixir & Infant Drops and Tempra Drops – pain killers contain non-kosher ingredients but may be used for infants & children unable to take tablets. Panadol & Panadeine also contain non-kosher ingredients. Their nature is such that the medications are acceptable for use by both children & adults.  ka

Comment: Should there be any doubt as to whether the fillets or cutlets have been cut with a clean knife, then the fish must be thoroughly washed in cold water before use.
Fresh fish must be recognizable as being a kosher species.

Jewish law therefore forbids the use of fillets which do not have the scaled skin attached & are not recognisable as being from a kosher species unless a rabbinic supervisor is present or the customer supervises the filleting of such fish. The supervisor should ensure that the knives and boards used are thoroughly clean before cutting commences.
